Job Description:
LeasePlan has been innovating on a global scale for more than 50 years. With around 1.7 million cars in over 30 countries, LeasePlan is the largest, most authoritative lease company of its kind in the world.

At LeasePlan Digital we are building innovative new software platforms, applications and enabling business models that will help define "what's next" for cars and mobility around the globe. It is a journey that will transform the current experience to a full digital experience. We are located in Amsterdam and are a growing international team.


Your role:

You will develop innovative back-end services (Java core 11+ and Spring) and help us stay up to date in our technology selection as the backend landscape continues to evolve. As a senior developer you will also help other backend developers grow through coaching, mentoring, and pair programming.

Your responsibilities:

Developing backend applications using Java core 11+ stack: design patterns, spring, JPA, web services, messaging, microservice architecture and docker;
Take ownership of services from development to deployment and maintenance
Supporting the LeasePlan backend community by giving talks on the company internal meetups;
Advocating for backend development best practices;
Developing people through coaching, mentoring, and management support;
Assisting our recruitment teams in finding the right people;
Doing whatever it takes to help LeasePlan Digital get the right solutions implemented to deliver value to customers around the globe, and
Ensure the goals and deliverables of the product team are met.


Your background and skills

We are looking for someone with a strong proficiency in Java core 11+ and Spring, as well as:

Extensive experience in developing RESTful APIs;
Experience with any Cloud platform (AWS/GCP/Azure/…);
Experience with Java build-tools, modern CI/CD, code versioning and QA tools and processes;
The confidence to speak up when you think something can be done better or smarter and the ability to accept compromises when necessary;
Familiar with working according the software development life cycle (SDLC);
The ability to translate business requirements into technical requirements, and
An agile mindset and experience with Scrum or other methodologies.


More About Us

LeasePlan Digital is a fast-moving business with a start-up culture that gives you the opportunity to apply your talents on a global scale. We are located in a new office surrounded by like-minded innovators at B.Amsterdam.

LeasePlan is committed to the uptake of electric vehicles and is a founding partner of EV100 - a new major global transport initiative designed to fast-track the uptake of electric vehicles among corporate companies. We are working to transform LeasePlan into a data-driven company that delivers any car, anytime, anywhere.

What's Next?

This is permanent role is based in Amsterdam. To apply, just upload your information via the link and apply directly. We are looking forward to exploring your opportunities with us!

